@node "Tips" "Tips and tricks"

 @{b}@{u}@{fg shine}Tips and tricks   @{ub}@{uu}@{fg text}

   * If you double click the "Sug" column, the sugested key will be
     put in the "Key" column.  NOTE:  If you got any key typed there it
     will be lost w/o any warning.  Of course you may double click the
     "Key" column too, and the action will be opposite.  Finally you may
     double click the "String" column to quickly exchange the keys.

   * @{b}Sugest single hotkey@{ub} works always, doesn't matter if you
     got a key defined or not. However it will always sugest you different
     key that this one you already have (because at first step it builds a
     table of used keys for own purposes and your defined key will treated
     as "InUse"). If you receive "R" (Not resolved - mostly happen when you
     work in Strict Mode) status, be sure that the key you got is the only
     one you can have for this string (of course if it will cause other
     error reports ;-)

   * If you often work with StrictMode turned off you may be interested
     in setting, let say, priority for each key stored in the bank.
     If you don't know yet, you have to have any hotkey bank loaded to
     make non strict mode running. Take any text editor and put most
     wanted keys on the begining of the line and less wanted at the end
     (for instance: in bank Alphanumeric letter 'a' is most important,
     while '9' will be used if any other key won't fit).


   That's all folks. Maybe you know more? 

@endnode

@node "Bugs" "Bugs"

 @{b}@{u}@{fg shine}Known bugs   @{ub}@{uu}@{fg text}

 As far as I know there's no serious bugs, however due
 to Murphy laws there have to be at least one, so if you
 get track of it, please inform @{" me " link "Credits" 0}


 @{b}@{u}@{fg shine}Problems I know about:   @{ub}@{uu}@{fg text}

 About window's scroll text may be partially unreadable with
 some fonts. This is not a bug, but kind of side effect caused by
 non-sizeable window making text object to always be sized to
 match the witdh of the logo image. Depending on the font's size
 it might appear much enough to fit all strings or too tall.  The
 only solution for you is to set taller or proportional font for the
 application in MUI preferences.  I might reedit the strings to short'em
 down, but don't expect it to happen to soon (if ever).

@endnode


